le, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 13.167577, "shard": "09", "shelf_id": "sn86075141, 1938-01-27, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/mthi", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["montana", "butte", "united states", "silver bow"], "subject_headings": ["United States--Montana--Silver Bow--Butte"], "subjects": [{"butte": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:butte&fo=json"}, {"montana": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:montana&fo=json"}, {"silver bow": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:silver+bow&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2023-07-06T04:23:50.176Z", "title": "Montana labor news (Butte, Mont.), January 27, 1938", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn86075141/1938-01-27/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86075141/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn86075141", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/a35a2ea6-7160-5b45-9e04-4c7aec4957e5"], "batch": ["mthi_horsetail_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["montana state federation of labor"], "date": "19??", "description": ["Weekly -v. 27, no. 6 (Feb. 8, 1951). \"Published Weekly in the Interests of Organized Labor.\" Issues for Aug. 8 and Aug. 15, 1946 both called v. 22, no. 22; actually constitute no. 23 and no. 24. Issues for Aug. 23, 1946-Mar. 13, 1947 called v. 22, no. 24-52; actually constitute no. 25-53. Issue for Dec. 30, 1948 called v. 24, no. 41; actually constitutes no. 42. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Official organ of: Montana State Federation of Labor. Description based on: Vol. 8, no. 7 (Apr. 28, 1932)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:15.450Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-01"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86075141/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [46.01284, -112.535583], "location": ["montana", "butte", "united states", "silver bow"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-112.535583, 46.01284], "number": ["microfilm master", "13472012", "online resource", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86075141/1951-02-08/ed-1/", "2831-4573", "duke univ libr", "2025-09-22t11:57:52.200000", "montana hist soc libr", "sn86075141", "1", "microfilm service copy", "772", "original", "2025-05-23t21:30:26", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86075141/1932-04-28/ed-1/", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["montana labor news (butte, mont.) 19??-1951", "chronicling america", "catalog", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 47.043335, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["newspapers", "butte (mont.)", "butte", "montana", "silver bow", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:20:06.081Z", "title": "Montana labor news", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn86075141/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218531/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1879", "dates": ["[1879 TO 1885]"], "description": ["Daily Began with vol. 1, no. 1 (August 5, 1879); ceased with vol. 6, no. 732 (May 24, 1885). Sunday edition called: Sunday miner. Vol. 1, no. 1 (August 5, 1879); title from masthead (newspaperarchive.com, viewed February 1, 2018). Vol. 6, no. 732 (May 24, 1885) (newspaperarchive.com, viewed February 1, 2018). Butte daily miner 2576-7135 (DLC) 2018218532 (OCoLC)958730662"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:21.806Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218531/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["montana", "butte", "united states", "silver bow"], "number": ["online resource", "2576-7062", "849807706", "2018218532", "2018218531", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["January 1, 1885 issue called: Holiday miner", "Sunday miner"], "partof": ["the daily miner (butte, montana) 1879-1885 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 37.836006, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD AN2 .B88", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "butte (mont.)", "butte", "montana", "silver bow", "periodicals", "electronic journals", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:55:54.213Z", "title": "The daily miner", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218531/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218532/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1885", "dates": ["[1885 TO 1899]"], "description": ["Daily Began with volume VI, no. 733 (May 26, 1885). Description based on: Volume VI, no. 733 (May 26, 1885); title from masthead (newspaperarchive.com, viewed February 1, 2018). Latest issue consulted: Volume XVII, whole number 12779 (April 2, 1888) (newspaperarchive.com, viewed February 1, 2018). Butte miner (Butte, Mont. : Daily)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:36.478Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218532/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["montana", "butte", "united states", "silver bow"], "number": ["958730662", "online resource", "2576-7135", "2018218531", "2018218532", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the butte daily miner (butte city, montana) 1885-18?? [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 37.836006, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "butte (mont.)", "butte", "montana", "silver bow", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:55:54.213Z", "title": "The Butte daily miner", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218532/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272186/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1901", "dates": ["[1901 TO 1912]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sun.) Began May 2, 1901; ceased -v. 29, no. 299 (Dec. 31, 1912). \"Republican.\" Cf. Ayer, 1912. Suspended: Feb. 13-Mar. 27, 1907. Description based on: Vol. XXI, no. 240 (January 2, 1902); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 18, 2013). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XXIII, no. 145 (December 31, 1903) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 18, 2013). Butte daily post (Online)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:23.371Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272186/", "image_url": [], "index": 9, "language": ["english"], "location": ["montana", "butte", "united states", "silver bow"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2013272186", "862977549", "2332-7510"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Butte intermountain"], "partof": ["the butte inter mountain (butte, montona) 1901-1912 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 37.836006, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "butte (mont.)", "butte", "montana", "silver bow", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:49:47.660Z", "title": "The Butte inter mountain", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013272186/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218270/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["metal trades council of butte (mont.)", "silver bow trades and labor assembly (mont.)", "montana world war veterans, inc", "montana state federation of labor", "state metal trades council (mont.)"], "date": "1918", "dates": ["[1918 TO 1921]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sun.) Began August 20, 1918; ceased v. 3, no. 244 (June 1, 1921). \"Independent.\" Motto: \"We preach the class struggle in the interests of the workers as a class.\" Suspended: Aug. 22-24, 1918, and Sept. 14, 1918. Available on microfilm from Micro Photo Division, Bell and Howell. Official organ of: Montana State Federation of Labor, National Trades Council of Butte, Silver Bow Trades and Labor Assembly, State Metal Trades Council, Feb. 25, 1920-June 1, 1921; Montana World War Veterans, Inc., Nov. 22, 1920-June 1, 1921. Description based on: Volume 1, number 129 (January 16, 1919); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 16, 2014). Latest issue consulted: Vol. III, no. 115 (December 31, 1920) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 16, 2014). Butte bulletin (Online)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:25.703Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218270/", "image_url": [], "index": 10, "language": ["english"], "location": ["montana", "butte", "united states", "silver bow"], "number": ["online resource", "876842153", "2372-2924", "2014218270", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the butte daily bulletin (butte, montana) 1918-1921 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 37.836006, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["working class", "newspapers", "butte", "montana", "silver bow", "united states", "labor"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:50:11.310Z", "title": "The Butte daily bulletin", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2014218270/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2013218599/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["dorsey, chris,", "duncan, john w.,"], "date": "1902", "dates": ["[1902 TO 1909]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. 1, no. 1 (May 30, 1902). Ceased by 1904. Editors: Chris Dorsey, May 30-<July 4>, 1902; John W. Duncan, May 30, 1902-<February 7, 1903>. \"Published in the interests of the colored people.\" Description based on: Vol. 1, no. 1 (May 30, 1902); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed Feb. 27, 2013). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 1, no. 32 (Feb. 7, 1903) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed Feb. 27, 2013)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:19.469Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013218599/", "image_url": [], "index": 11, "language": ["english"], "location": ["montana", "butte", "united states", "silver bow"], "number": ["828631031", "online resour